<http://www.spektrix.com/tidemarktheatre/event/55001AMSBLSDPDNMRVSMJKRHLNGCNQBMH>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Crash Test Dummies";
  schema:description """
	With one of the most recognizable voices in Canadian music, Crash Test Dummies return to the Tidemark Theatre on November 12th with their <span class=\"ItalicText\">Jingle All the Way</span> holiday tour.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Rising to international fame in the early ’90s, the band made their mark with hits like Mmm, Mmm, Mmm, Mmm and Superman’s Song, songs that still resonate decades later thanks to their distinctive sound and the unmistakable baritone of Brad Roberts. Blending folk influences with alternative rock, their live show leans into what they do best: thoughtful songwriting, tight musicianship, and a sound that’s instantly familiar but never dated.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Expect a mix of fan favourites, seasonal touches, and the kind of understated, powerful performance that has kept audiences coming back for over 30 years.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Opening the night is Logan Richard, a rising East Coast artist whose sound moves easily between blues, folk, pop, and soul. Known for his smooth vocals and impressive guitar work, the PEI-based musician has spent years performing across Canada both as a solo artist and alongside some of the country’s top musicians. His latest album, Character Traits, highlights his versatility as a songwriter while bringing a fresh, modern edge to classic singer-songwriter storytelling.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Tickets: $57 Admission <span class=\"ItalicText\">(+applicable taxes & fees)</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-11-12T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
